# üß≠ Linux Management Master Chart

> A complete guide to understand how Linux is managed ‚Äî from users and processes to storage, networking, security, and automation.

---

## üèóÔ∏è Overview

Linux management revolves around **controlling, maintaining, securing, and automating** all system components:
- **Users & Permissions**
- **Processes & Services**
- **Files & Storage**
- **Network & Security**
- **Packages & Updates**
- **Automation & Monitoring**

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ USER & ACCESS MANAGEMENT

| Component | Description | Important Commands |
|------------|--------------|--------------------|
| **User Management** | Create, modify, or delete user accounts | `useradd`, `usermod`, `userdel`, `passwd` |
| **Group Management** | Manage multiple users under groups | `groupadd`, `gpasswd`, `/etc/group` |
| **Privileges** | Control admin access | `sudo`, `su`, `visudo`, `/etc/sudoers` |
| **Access Control** | File permissions & ownership | `chmod`, `chown`, `chgrp`, `umask` |
| **Advanced Security** | ACLs & Mandatory Access Control | `getfacl`, `setfacl`, `SELinux`, `AppArmor` |

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ PROCESS MANAGEMENT

| Aspect | Description | Commands |
|--------|--------------|----------|
| **Viewing Processes** | List and monitor running processes | `ps`, `top`, `htop`, `pgrep` |
| **Killing Processes** | Stop or restart processes | `kill`, `pkill`, `killall` |
| **Priority Control** | Adjust CPU priority | `nice`, `renice` |
| **Background Jobs** | Manage running tasks | `jobs`, `fg`, `bg` |
| **Scheduling** | Run jobs automatically | `cron`, `at`, `batch` |
| **Systemd Services** | Manage system daemons | `systemctl`, `journalctl` |

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ FILE & STORAGE MANAGEMENT

| Area | Description | Commands |
|------|--------------|----------|
| **File System Hierarchy** | Structure of directories | `/bin`, `/etc`, `/home`, `/var`, `/dev` |
| **Disk Partitioning** | Manage disks and partitions | `fdisk`, `parted`, `lsblk` |
| **Mounting** | Mount/unmount devices | `mount`, `umount`, `/etc/fstab` |
| **Disk Usage** | Monitor space usage | `df -h`, `du -sh`, `iostat` |
| **Permissions** | Manage ownership and access | `chmod`, `chown`, `chgrp` |
| **Backup & Compression** | Copy and archive data | `tar`, `gzip`, `rsync`, `dd` |
| **Advanced Storage** | Logical volumes and RAID | `lvm`, `mdadm`, `quota` |

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ NETWORK MANAGEMENT

| Function | Description | Commands |
|-----------|--------------|----------|
| **Configuration** | Set IPs and routes | `ip`, `ifconfig`, `nmcli` |
| **Connectivity** | Test and diagnose | `ping`, `traceroute`, `curl`, `wget` |
| **Name Resolution** | Check DNS and host lookup | `nslookup`, `dig` |
| **Ports & Sockets** | Check listening ports | `netstat`, `ss`, `lsof -i` |
| **Remote Access** | Connect and transfer files | `ssh`, `scp`, `sftp`, `rsync` |
| **Firewall** | Manage access control | `ufw`, `iptables`, `firewalld` |
| **Network Services** | DNS, DHCP, File sharing | `systemctl restart network`, `nfs`, `samba` |

---

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ PACKAGE & SOFTWARE MANAGEMENT

| Type | Description | Commands |
|------|--------------|----------|
| **APT (Debian/Ubuntu)** | Package installation | `apt update`, `apt install`, `dpkg -l` |
| **DNF/YUM (RHEL/Fedora)** | RPM-based management | `dnf install`, `yum remove`, `rpm -qa` |
| **Pacman (Arch)** | Arch package manager | `pacman -Syu`, `pacman -R` |
| **Manual Build** | Compile from source | `./configure`, `make`, `make install` |
| **Repositories** | Configure software sources | `/etc/apt/sources.list`, `/etc/yum.repos.d/` |

---

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ SYSTEM PERFORMANCE & MONITORING

| Category | Tools | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| **CPU & Memory** | `top`, `htop`, `vmstat`, `free`, `uptime` | Resource utilization |
| **Disk I/O** | `iostat`, `df`, `du` | Disk monitoring |
| **Logs** | `journalctl`, `dmesg`, `/var/log/` | View system logs |
| **Benchmarking** | `stress`, `sysbench`, `ioping` | Test performance |
| **Tuning** | `sysctl`, `swapoff`, `swapon` | Optimize system behavior |

---

## 7Ô∏è‚É£ SECURITY MANAGEMENT

| Area | Focus | Commands |
|------|--------|----------|
| **File Security** | Permissions and ACLs | `chmod`, `setfacl`, `ls -l` |
| **Network Security** | Firewall & Intrusion Prevention | `ufw`, `iptables`, `fail2ban` |
| **Authentication** | Manage login security | `passwd`, `ssh-keygen`, `pam_tally2` |
| **Auditing** | Track system activity | `auditd`, `ausearch`, `aureport` |
| **SELinux/AppArmor** | Enforce security policies | `getenforce`, `setenforce`, `aa-status` |

---

## 8Ô∏è‚É£ AUTOMATION & SCHEDULING

| Type | Description | Commands |
|------|--------------|----------|
| **Shell Scripting** | Automate tasks | `bash`, `echo`, `if`, `for`, `while` |
| **Cron Jobs** | Recurring tasks | `crontab -e`, `/etc/cron.*` |
| **One-time Tasks** | Schedule once | `at`, `batch` |
| **Configuration Automation** | Manage many systems | `ansible`, `puppet`, `chef` |

---

## 9Ô∏è‚É£ SYSTEM MAINTENANCE

| Task | Purpose | Tools |
|------|----------|-------|
| **System Updates** | Keep system current | `apt upgrade`, `dnf update` |
| **Log Rotation** | Manage growing logs | `logrotate`, `/etc/logrotate.conf` |
| **Backup & Restore** | Data protection | `rsync`, `tar`, `cron` |
| **Kernel Management** | Update & view kernel | `uname -r`, `modprobe`, `lsmod` |
| **Troubleshooting** | Diagnose issues | `dmesg`, `systemctl status`, `strace`, `lsof` |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è SUMMARY TABLE

| Management Area | Description | Core Tools |
|-----------------|--------------|-------------|
| üë§ User Management | Users, groups, sudoers | `useradd`, `sudo`, `chown` |
| ‚öôÔ∏è Process Control | Tasks, daemons, jobs | `ps`, `systemctl`, `cron` |
| üìÅ File & Disk | Partitions, permissions | `df`, `lsblk`, `chmod`, `mount` |
| üåê Network | IPs, ports, firewall | `ip`, `ss`, `ufw`, `ssh` |
| üì¶ Packages | Software management | `apt`, `dnf`, `make` |
| üìä Monitoring | Logs, performance | `top`, `journalctl`, `vmstat` |
| üîí Security | Hardening, ACLs | `SELinux`, `iptables`, `auditd` |
| ü§ñ Automation | Scripting & scheduling | `bash`, `crontab`, `ansible` |
| üîÅ Maintenance | Updates, logs, recovery | `logrotate`, `rsync`, `systemctl` |

---

## üß© Tip: How to Master Linux Management

1. üß† **Understand the architecture** ‚Üí Know what each layer (user, kernel, hardware) does  
2. ‚öôÔ∏è **Use terminal daily** ‚Üí Replace GUI tools  
3. üõ†Ô∏è **Practice system tasks** ‚Üí Create users, mount drives, monitor logs  
4. üîí **Secure your system** ‚Üí Manage permissions, firewall, and SSH keys  
5. ü§ñ **Automate repetitive tasks** ‚Üí Learn Bash and cron  
6. üìà **Monitor performance** ‚Üí Keep system stable and optimized  

